The subject consists of many interesting thematic blocks. In the first lectures, the main focus is on Chinese historical periodization and chronology. After that, the three fundamental schools of Chinese culture are discussed - confucianism, taoism and buddhism. Following lectures introduce different aspects of Chinese culture, e.g chinese languages, mythology, art, music and film. Besides the lectures, we will listen to Chinese music and watch Chinese movies.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the subject is to give an overview of the most important aspects of Chinese culture and society. Both, traditional and modern China, are under discussion.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student who has passed this subject knows: *	The basic concepts and most important aspects of Chinese culture *	Administrative divisions of China *	Periodization and chronology of Chinese history *	Base texts of chinese culture *	The difference between traditional and modern Chinese culture
